Chipset Evolution
	Chipsets used to consist of two primary chips
		Northbridge originally handled RAM						
		Southbridge handled expansion devices	[[img https://images.hothardware.com/static/articleimages/Item845/p965_block.png]]
	and a Super I/O chip for legacy devices			[[img https://images.anandtech.com/reviews/cpu/intel/SNBE/X79_blockdiagram.jpg]]
	CPU now handles a lot of what the chipset used to		[[img https://www.techpowerup.com/review/intel-core-i7-10700k/images/arch6.jpg]]
	Block diagrams on the right show the evolution of the chipsets
		Intel
			Core 2
			2nd  Generation i7
			10th Generation i7
		AMD
			APU (Accelerated Processing Unit)
				APUs a marketing term for a combined CPU/GPU 
